 Anything","2019-05-19 15:52:00",{"url":998,"title":999,"date":1000},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F19\u002Fjs-weird-world-28-pass-by-value-vs-reference\u002F","[JS Weird World] No.28 A Quick Reminder: Pass by Value vs Pass by Reference","2019-05-19 12:13:00",[1002,1007,1012],{"url":1003,"title":1004,"date":1005,"readingMinutes":1006},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F27\u002Fjs-weird-world-bonus-closures\u002F","[JS Weird World] Bonus: Closures, One More Time","2019-05-27 13:50:04","5",{"url":1008,"title":1009,"date":1010,"readingMinutes":1011},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F25\u002Fjs-weird-world-68-the-end-is-a-new-beginning\u002F","[JS Weird World] No.68 Wrapping Up the Weird Parts of JavaScript","2019-05-25 16:36:00","1",{"url":1013,"title":1014,"date":1015,"readingMinutes":1016},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F25\u002Fjs-weird-world-67-adding-jquery-support\u002F","[JS Weird World] No.67 Adding jQuery Support to Our Mini Framework","2019-05-25 16:19:00","2",1784013063588]